Sprint Cup Series drivers race past the start/finish line during the second lap of a NASCAR auto race at Kansas Speedway in Kansas City, Kan., Sunday, Oct. 18, 2015. (AP Photo/Orlin Wagner) Posted: Sunday, October 18, 2015 10:48 pm | Updated: 11:15 pm, Sun Oct 18, 2015. 
KANSAS CITY, Kan. (AP) — Joey Logano kept peeking around Matt Kenseth as the laps ticked away at Kansas Speedway, the two of them in entirely different situations in the Chase for the Sprint Cup championship.
